      • removeItem

        public void removeItem​(SystemComponent item)
        Description copied from class: CategorizedContainer
        Tag an item for removal from this container's item list. The item will be effectively removed only when effectChanges() or effectAllChanges() is called thereafter. This enables one to keep the container state consistent over time in discrete time simulations.
        Specified by:

      • removeItemNow

        public void removeItemNow​(SystemComponent item)
        CAUTION: This method is only here to handle removal of SystemComponents that jumped out of their space. As this cannot be handled in the usual effectChanges() method, it is done here. It should NEVER be used for anything else.

      • effectChanges

        public void effectChanges​(java.util.Collection<SystemComponent>... changedLists)
        Description copied from interface: DynamicContainer
        Effectively remove and add items from the container lists (before a call to this method, they are just stored into itemsToRemove and itemsToAdd). NB: to recursively effect changes for all sub-containers, use effectAllChanges(). The arguments are here in case a return list of items is needed - depends on context of course
